column5:
@peter m, to me 2 weeks in dubai alone would be a little too much. i have been to dubai as a female solo traveller for 7 days about 4 years ago and i felt that it was just nice. i did not visit a.d. but as advised by the others, it might be a good choice to visit there for say, 3 nights or so. on my trip to dubai, i visited the dubai opera, dubai aquarium at the dubai mall, and had dinner near the dubai fountain on day 1. the dubai fountain is beautiful in the evening. on day 2, i went to skydive dubai and dubai miracle garden. on day 3 morning, i went for the desert tour whereby i got to take the 4 x 4 dunes ride and the camel ride. in the afternoon, i took a stroll along the sunset beach where i saw the burj al arab very clearly at the other end. i went to ski dubai on day 4 and it took up almost the whole day. it was my first ski experience and i enjoyed it very much although it was artificial snow. i spent a day at dubai creek on day 5 exploring the old dubai. on day 6, i went to the burj khalifa's observation deck in the morning and talise ottoman hamman spa on the palm in the afternoon. i am still reminiscing the spa i had until now, it was that great! last day was just a rest and relax day strolling around the city area.
i guess it depends what type of solo traveller you are. i think the itinerary i had was a well mix of everything - adventure, heritage and culture, nature at the gardens and beaches, relaxation etc.
edited: 4:16 am, april 22, 2021

