since you mentioned skiing for "a few days," you might not want to base yourself at tokyo and take repeated day trips? if that's the case, karuizawa makes the most sense since there is something to see/do in the town and nearby places for non-skiers.
if you opt for day trips from tokyo, a tokyo wide pass could offer the best value since you get 3 consecutive days of unlimited rides to karuizawa or yuzawa. they also offer discounts for ski lifts for gala yuzawa: 
christmas to new year's is normally peak season with much more expensive rates, especially when availability dwindles. i suggest you book your accommodation early as long as you don't have to prepay.

